10
00:01:22,559 --> 00:01:23,120
Where is the phone?

11
00:01:23,879 --> 00:01:24,639
I don't have it on me.

12
00:01:24,959 --> 00:01:25,559
It was sent back to the station.

13
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:26,440
It needs to be dusted for prints.

14
00:01:26,599 --> 00:01:27,440
Then what are we waiting for?

15
00:01:27,599 --> 00:01:28,239
Hurry up, let's go.

16
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:35,800
You're here.

17
00:01:36,239 --> 00:01:36,639
How is it?

18
00:01:36,919 --> 00:01:37,839
Ready to get off work?

19
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:39,959
I'll be done in a second.

20
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:45,919
What are you so happy about?

21
00:01:45,919 --> 00:01:46,760
You're smiling so much.

22
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:47,440
Let's go.

23
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,279
I'll take you to a

24
00:01:48,279 --> 00:01:49,720
really delicious place to eat.

25
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,040
What place is so delicious?

26
00:01:52,559 --> 00:01:53,319
It's a place that over the years,

27
00:01:53,519 --> 00:01:55,040
I've wanted to take you back to.

28
00:01:55,559 --> 00:01:56,319
Where?

29
00:01:56,919 --> 00:01:58,319
Come to the parking lot when you're ready.

30
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:05,919
This dish is good.

31
00:02:06,080 --> 00:02:06,680
It's good, right?

32
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:11,759
So this is the mysterious place you mentioned.

33
00:02:12,399 --> 00:02:13,479
Why do I feel like I've been here?

34
00:02:13,839 --> 00:02:14,279
It's quite familiar.

35
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,679
You really don't remember.

36
00:02:17,279 --> 00:02:18,240
Back when we were sophomores,

37
00:02:18,559 --> 00:02:19,720
we visited the city museum together.

38
00:02:20,399 --> 00:02:21,919
After that, we came to this restaurant.

39
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:23,600
Did you forget?

40
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,440
You wanted to eat spicy food every day back then.

41
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:28,839
Right.

42
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,160
So this is where we came.

43
00:02:31,479 --> 00:02:32,960
How is your memory so good?

44
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:34,039
I've almost forgotten everything.

45
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:35,679
It's not that my memory is good.

46
00:02:36,839 --> 00:02:37,759
It's because that day,

47
00:02:38,279 --> 00:02:39,440
I finally made up my mind

48
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:41,440
to confess my feelings,

49
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:42,720
but I couldn't say it out loud.

50
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:45,759
It's the anniversary of my failure.

51
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:47,839
Confess?

52
00:02:49,759 --> 00:02:50,600
To me?

53
00:02:51,279 --> 00:02:52,199
Who else but you?

54
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:55,080
I was so nervous my mouth went dry.

55
00:02:57,279 --> 00:02:58,279
Stop joking around.

56
00:02:58,600 --> 00:02:59,119
Come on.

57
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:00,279
Eat something.

58
00:03:00,279 --> 00:03:01,520
Before, because of Du Zheng,

59
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:04,160
I could only stand aside and silently wish you well.

60
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:05,880
But not anymore.

61
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,600
I will give you a better life.

62
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,320
I want to be a man capable of making money,

63
00:03:10,559 --> 00:03:12,199
so you won't have to worry about work anymore.

64
00:03:13,399 --> 00:03:14,399
So that for the rest of your life,

65
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:15,559
you'll have nothing to worry about.

66
00:03:18,639 --> 00:03:19,600
What are you talking about?

67
00:03:22,919 --> 00:03:23,759
I don't believe

68
00:03:24,039 --> 00:03:25,279
you haven't felt my feelings at all.

69
00:03:25,679 --> 00:03:27,360
I wanted to tell you some good news today.

70
00:03:28,119 --> 00:03:29,360
I'm going to be the Chief Executive Officer.

71
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,160
Really?

72
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:33,639
My happiness

73
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:35,039
must be shared with you.

74
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,080
Congratulations.

75
00:03:37,679 --> 00:03:38,360
Also,

76
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,600
the next time I see you,

77
00:03:41,759 --> 00:03:42,720
I won't hesitate anymore.

78
00:03:46,279 --> 00:03:48,479
I heard Gu Rongchen's health is getting worse.

79
00:03:49,199 --> 00:03:51,000
His Sepsis is about to flare up.

80
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,479
He probably won't last much longer.

81
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,360
So I think

82
00:03:56,639 --> 00:03:58,000
we can adjust our strategy.

83
00:03:58,679 --> 00:03:59,399
What strategy?

84
00:04:00,199 --> 00:04:01,240
The relevant departments

85
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,600
have already started investigating.

86
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,440
During the investigation,

87
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:06,839
he will be forbidden from contacting anyone.

88
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:11,199
How can they do that?

89
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:13,440
Before a person dies,

90
00:04:13,919 --> 00:04:15,199
they should always be with their family.

91
00:04:15,759 --> 00:04:16,600
Exactly.

92
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:18,399
Even if it's for his family,

93
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:20,920
he should agree to sign it, right?

94
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:23,559
Che Li,

95
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:25,720
about this matter,

96
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,839
can we not do this?

97
00:04:28,119 --> 00:04:29,079
What are you hesitating for?

98
00:04:29,839 --> 00:04:31,239
Why have you become so weak?

99
00:04:32,119 --> 00:04:33,600
The guarantee letter is already drafted.

100
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,079
Nelson,

101
00:04:35,079 --> 00:04:36,640
you go to him personally tomorrow to get it signed.

102
00:04:40,359 --> 00:04:42,119
Tomorrow is the day of our success.

103
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,679
At this crucial moment,

104
00:04:45,399 --> 00:04:47,440
you, Nelson, should handle it personally.

105
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:49,480
Right?

106
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:57,839
Senior.

107
00:04:58,679 --> 00:04:59,239
Senior.

108
00:04:59,399 --> 00:05:00,440
You finally showed up.

109
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:01,760
The mastermind Tan Feng mentioned,

110
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:02,959
there's hope of finding them now.

111
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:06,600
The mastermind behind the Raw Material Case?

112
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:07,119
Yes.

113
00:05:08,119 --> 00:05:09,239
I checked the call logs.

114
00:05:09,959 --> 00:05:10,760
Tan Feng used this phone

115
00:05:10,959 --> 00:05:12,200
to contact only one number.

116
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:32,119
Where did you go?

117
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,000
I couldn't find you anywhere.

118
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:36,119
Was it...

119
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:38,559
Was it Ziang?

120
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:43,519
So you're saying,

121
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,880
to investigate the company's Raw Material Case,

122
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:48,200
you used another phone

123
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:50,000
to contact Tan Feng separately, right?

124
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:51,399
Yes.

125
00:05:52,279 --> 00:05:54,119
This banned raw material incident

126
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:55,440
is very sensitive within the company.

127
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:57,399
So to prevent information from leaking,

128
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,160
I used a separate phone

129
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,600
to contact Tan Feng.

130
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:01,559
Then tell me,

131
00:06:02,119 --> 00:06:03,279
who is the mastermind behind this?

132
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:04,119
The mastermind?

133
00:06:04,279 --> 00:06:05,000
Yes.

134
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:06,359
Isn't it obvious?

135
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,440
Tan Feng was acting on someone's orders.

136
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,519
With his limited abilities,

137
00:06:11,359 --> 00:06:13,040
how could he tamper with the raw materials?

138
00:06:13,519 --> 00:06:14,519
And if he wasn't

139
00:06:14,519 --> 00:06:16,359
colluding with the company's top management,

140
00:06:16,799 --> 00:06:18,519
how could he have easily escaped

141
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,679
during the commission of the crime?

142
00:06:20,279 --> 00:06:22,760
Since you investigated the Raw Material Case,

143
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,559
then tell me,

144
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,640
what exactly is going on?

145
00:06:29,519 --> 00:06:30,880
From the company's perspective,

146
00:06:31,559 --> 00:06:33,160
rather than investigating the mastermind,

147
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,799
calming this storm is the most important thing.

148
00:06:36,679 --> 00:06:37,279
Therefore,

149
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:39,559
I had Tan Feng use a separate phone too,

150
00:06:40,239 --> 00:06:42,160
and imposed controls on the relevant personnel.

151
00:06:44,119 --> 00:06:45,600
You didn't answer my question.

152
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,480
Then you answer one of my questions first.

153
00:06:48,839 --> 00:06:49,399
Okay.

154
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:50,519
What does this matter

155
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:51,920
have to do with

156
00:06:52,359 --> 00:06:53,119
Du Zheng's death?

157
00:06:53,239 --> 00:06:53,799
